But in any case, it was a day.

27:46.818 --> 27:50.784
When, you know, the kids didn't have to do their schoolwork at our house.

27:50.884 --> 27:53.989
It was the day when they didn't have to do their normal kinds of chores.

27:54.810 --> 28:07.669
The Sabbath day was the day of pleasure in the enjoyment of God and God's people and rest and fellowship and all that kind of stuff.

28:07.869 --> 28:16.562
And one Saturday night, Melinda asked me what I wanted for Sunday dinner.

28:16.834 --> 28:17.755
that next morning.

28:17.775 --> 28:26.567
And this was after a long holiday season in which we had a variety of feasts already.

28:26.587 --> 28:29.391
And I threw our curveball.

28:29.411 --> 28:36.601
I said, you know, we feasted for so long on seafood and ham and turkey and rich desserts.

28:36.761 --> 28:39.164
I was craving something lighter.

28:39.264 --> 28:43.009
And so I said to her, surprisingly, how about a salad?

28:44.371 --> 28:46.354
And well, she went along with me.

28:46.530 --> 28:56.352
And then poor Caleb, young Caleb, our son, leaned over during worship and said, in a whisper, what's for dinner?

28:57.615 --> 29:00.382
And she just told him, you don't want to know.

29:02.426 --> 29:05.874
The interruption of the ritual is jarring.

29:06.594 --> 29:08.878
But we were together, so it was okay.

29:08.898 --> 29:13.446
In the South, I'm sure it was fabulous, but it wasn't a roasted gravy.

29:13.907 --> 29:28.191
But in any case, Leviticus is giving us this graphic visual aid and rituals that help the people of God taste God's grace and then express their faith in concrete ways.

29:29.493 --> 29:32.178
And there's reality behind the rituals.

29:32.834 --> 29:41.726
And for most of us, we've inherited Christianity concerned with the internal, the reflective, the cognitive.

29:41.766 --> 29:46.413
We're all in our head or in our brain or navel gazing or such.

29:47.053 --> 29:52.601
And yet, Leviticus comes to us with the blood and guts of Christianity, literally.

29:53.062 --> 30:02.034
And as another pastor put it, instead of a treatise on the nature of the kingdom of death and its opposition to the kingdom of life,

30:02.754 --> 30:10.142
Instead, God instructs his people with strange skin diseases to steer clear of the temple until they're clean.

30:10.162 --> 30:19.893
And instead of trying to describe a very abstract idea like substitutionary atonement, Leviticus instead gives you instructions on how to slit the throat of the lamb.

30:19.933 --> 30:31.026
The picture of blood splattering on your clothes as the lamb is placed on the fire, lends vivid imagery to the penalty of sin.

30:31.298 --> 30:40.928
The entire sacrificial system becomes one giant prop of visual aid to find out what it means to truly be in relationship with God.

30:41.568 --> 30:50.177
And we might say in the way in which God has commanded and in the way in which God has invited us.

30:50.257 --> 30:59.506
So this reality behind the ritual praise God Jesus has fulfilled that which has been taught and

30:59.682 --> 31:00.163
promise.

31:00.183 --> 31:19.275
So I'd invite you to stick around the next many months as we plow through Leviticus that we might see Jesus better together and see the rich foreshadowing it gives us of the glory of Christ.

31:20.236 --> 31:22.400
Let's pray together.

31:22.420 --> 31:23.602
Father, thank you.

31:23.874 --> 31:35.305
that you are a God who dwells with His people and that Jesus is God incarnate, God in the flesh, the true tabernacle of God.

31:35.325 --> 31:52.082
Thank you that He's our true high priest who offered the one true final perfect sacrifice of atonement for our sins to reconcile us to you and you to us.

31:52.610 --> 31:55.964
And so we would see Jesus, Lord, help us in that.

31:56.225 --> 31:57.250
In His name I pray.

31:58.495 --> 31:58.877
Amen.

31:59.741 --> 32:00.062
Amen.

32:00.303 --> 32:01.970
Let's stand together and sing.

